      <div class="legal-section">
        <h2>2. Definitions</h2>
        <p>In these Terms, the following definitions apply:</p>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>APRC:</strong> Annual Percentage Rate of Charge, a standardised measure of the total cost of a mortgage expressed as an annual percentage, as required by MCOB.</li>
          <li><strong>Consumer Duty:</strong> The FCA's Consumer Duty (PS22/9), which requires firms to act to deliver good outcomes for retail customers, including acting in good faith, avoiding foreseeable harm, and enabling customers to pursue their financial objectives.</li>
          <li><strong>EPM (Equity Preservation Mortgage):</strong> A secured mortgage product offered by FutureProof whereby the Borrower borrows against residential property equity, the loan proceeds are invested in a diversified portfolio of index-linked ETFs and fixed income instruments with hedging collars, and the Borrower receives monthly income from investment returns while preserving property equity.</li>
          <li><strong>FCA:</strong> The Financial Conduct Authority, the financial services regulator for the United Kingdom.</li>
          <li><strong>FOS:</strong> The Financial Ombudsman Service, an independent body that resolves disputes between consumers and financial services firms.</li>
          <li><strong>FSCS:</strong> The Financial Services Compensation Scheme, the UK's statutory compensation scheme for customers of authorised financial services firms.</li>
          <li><strong>Hedging Collar:</strong> A risk management strategy using protective put options and covered call options to limit downside investment risk while retaining upside potential within a defined range.</li>
          <li><strong>Holiday Mechanism:</strong> A feature of the EPM that allows the Borrower to temporarily suspend monthly income payments under specified conditions.</li>
          <li><strong>Key Facts Illustration (KFI):</strong> A personalised document required by MCOB 5.6 that sets out the key features, costs, and risks of a specific mortgage product.</li>
          <li><strong>Lifetime Mortgage:</strong> A type of equity release product regulated by the FCA. The EPM differs from a traditional lifetime mortgage in that it is designed for a fixed term (10-30 years) rather than the lifetime of the borrower, and it provides monthly income from invested proceeds rather than a lump sum.</li>
          <li><strong>LTV (Loan-to-Value):</strong> The ratio of the mortgage loan to the appraised value of the property, expressed as a percentage.</li>
          <li><strong>MCOB:</strong> Mortgages and Home Finance: Conduct of Business sourcebook, part of the FCA Handbook, setting out rules for firms that carry on home finance activities.</li>
          <li><strong>NNEG (No Negative Equity Guarantee):</strong> A guarantee ensuring that the Borrower will never owe more than the value of their property at the time of repayment.</li>
          <li><strong>Platform:</strong> The FutureProof Financial website, web application, and any associated digital services at futureprooffinancial.co.</li>
          <li><strong>Profit Share:</strong> A mechanism whereby surplus investment returns above the required income and costs are shared between the Borrower and FutureProof at predetermined intervals.</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div class="legal-section">
        <h2>3. Service Description</h2>
        <p><strong>3.1</strong> FutureProof provides an Equity Preservation Mortgage (EPM) product that enables eligible homeowners aged 55 and over to:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>(a) Borrow against residential property equity up to a maximum LTV of <%= (config["max_ltv"].to_f * 100).to_i %>%;</li>
          <li>(b) Have loan proceeds invested in a diversified portfolio comprising approximately 70% S&amp;P 500 index-linked ETFs and approximately 30% fixed income instruments;</li>
          <li>(c) Benefit from hedging collar protection to limit downside investment risk;</li>
          <li>(d) Receive monthly income of approximately 1.5% of property value per annum from investment returns;</li>
          <li>(e) Preserve 100% of property equity through the NNEG insurance mechanism;</li>
          <li>(f) Participate in profit-sharing every 5 years when investment returns exceed required thresholds.</li>
        </ul>
        <p><strong>3.2</strong> The Platform provides tools for obtaining indicative quotes, submitting applications, uploading supporting documentation, tracking application progress, and managing your EPM account.</p>
        <p><strong>3.3</strong> All quotes, projections, and estimates provided through the Platform are indicative only and are subject to formal property valuation, credit assessment, affordability assessment, and lender approval.</p>
      </div>

