      <div class="legal-section">
        <h2>5. Eligibility</h2>
        <p><strong>5.1</strong> To be eligible for an EPM, you must satisfy all of the following criteria:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>(a) Be aged 55 years or over at the time of application;</li>
          <li>(b) Be a UK resident (including England, Wales, Scotland, and Northern Ireland);</li>
          <li>(c) Own residential property in the United Kingdom with a minimum value of <%= config["currency_symbol"] %><%= number_with_delimiter(config["min_home_value"]) %>;</li>
          <li>(d) The property must be your primary residence;</li>
          <li>(e) The property must have a clear or acceptable title registered with HM Land Registry (or Registers of Scotland, or Land and Property Services in Northern Ireland);</li>
          <li>(f) Have legal capacity to enter into a mortgage contract;</li>
          <li>(g) Not be an undischarged bankrupt or subject to an Individual Voluntary Arrangement (IVA), Debt Relief Order (DRO), or sequestration (Scotland);</li>
          <li>(h) Pass our credit assessment and affordability checks as required by MCOB.</li>
        </ul>
        <p><strong>5.2</strong> Additional considerations may apply for properties in Scotland (where Scots property law applies) and Northern Ireland. We will advise you of any jurisdiction-specific requirements during the application process.</p>
        <p><strong>5.3</strong> Leasehold properties must have a minimum unexpired lease term sufficient to exceed the proposed EPM term by at least 30 years.</p>
        <p><strong>5.4</strong> We reserve the right to decline applications that do not meet our lending criteria, in accordance with responsible lending obligations.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="legal-section">
        <h2>6. Account Registration</h2>
        <p><strong>6.1</strong> You must create an account on the Platform to access our services and apply for an EPM.</p>
        <p><strong>6.2</strong> You agree to provide accurate, complete, and current information during registration and throughout the application process. Providing false or misleading information may constitute a criminal offence under the Fraud Act 2006.</p>
        <p><strong>6.3</strong> You are responsible for maintaining the confidentiality and security of your account credentials, including your password and any multi-factor authentication tokens.</p>
        <p><strong>6.4</strong> You must notify us immediately if you become aware of any unauthorised use of your account.</p>
        <p><strong>6.5</strong> We may require identity verification, including but not limited to passport, driving licence, proof of address, and biometric verification, in compliance with our regulatory obligations.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="legal-section">
        <h2>7. EPM Product Terms</h2>
        <p><strong>7.1</strong> The key features of the EPM product are as follows:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>(a) <strong>Maximum Loan-to-Value:</strong> <%= (config["max_ltv"].to_f * 100).to_i %>% of the independently assessed property value;</li>
          <li>(b) <strong>Loan Terms:</strong> 10, 15, 20, 25, or 30 years;</li>
          <li>(c) <strong>Monthly Income:</strong> Approximately 1.5% of property value per annum, derived from investment returns, subject to market performance;</li>
          <li>(d) <strong>Investment Strategy:</strong> Diversified portfolio of approximately 70% S&amp;P 500 index-linked ETFs and 30% fixed income instruments, protected by hedging collars;</li>
          <li>(e) <strong>Equity Preservation:</strong> 100% of property equity is preserved through the NNEG insurance mechanism;</li>
          <li>(f) <strong>Profit Share:</strong> Surplus investment returns are shared between the Borrower and FutureProof every 5 years, in accordance with the profit-sharing schedule set out in your mortgage offer.</li>
        </ul>
        <p><strong>7.2</strong> The EPM is a secured loan. Your property is used as security for the mortgage. If you fail to comply with the terms of the mortgage, your property may be repossessed.</p>
        <p><strong>7.3</strong> YOUR HOME MAY BE REPOSSESSED IF YOU DO NOT KEEP UP REPAYMENTS ON YOUR MORTGAGE OR ANY OTHER DEBT SECURED ON IT.</p>
        <p><strong>7.4</strong> The specific terms of your EPM, including the interest rate, APRC, fees, monthly income amount, and repayment terms, will be set out in your individual mortgage offer and Key Facts Illustration.</p>
        <p><strong>7.5</strong> At the end of the mortgage term, the loan principal is repaid from the investment portfolio. Any surplus is returned to you. If the investment portfolio is insufficient, the NNEG insurance and pool mechanisms cover the shortfall.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="legal-section">
        <h2>8. FCA Consumer Duty Obligations</h2>
        <p><strong>8.1</strong> In accordance with the FCA Consumer Duty (PS22/9), we are committed to delivering good outcomes for our customers. This includes:</p>

        <h3>8.1.1 Acting in Good Faith</h3>
        <p>We will act honestly, fairly, and professionally in all our dealings with you. We will not exploit your trust, vulnerability, or lack of knowledge.</p>

        <h3>8.1.2 Avoiding Foreseeable Harm</h3>
        <p>We design our products and services to avoid causing foreseeable harm. We conduct ongoing monitoring to identify and mitigate potential risks to customers, including investment risk, affordability risk, and the risk of property repossession.</p>

        <h3>8.1.3 Enabling and Supporting Customers</h3>
        <p>We provide clear, timely, and accessible information to enable you to make informed decisions about the EPM product. We support customers who may be in vulnerable circumstances, in accordance with FCA Guidance FG21/1.</p>

        <h3>8.1.4 Price and Value</h3>
        <p>We ensure that the price of our products and services represents fair value to customers. We conduct regular fair value assessments and will notify you of any material changes to fees or charges.</p>

        <p><strong>8.2</strong> If at any point we determine that the EPM product is not suitable for you, we will inform you and, where appropriate, decline your application or recommend alternative options.</p>
