        <h2>16. Affordability Assessment</h2>
        <p><strong>16.1</strong> In accordance with MCOB requirements, we will conduct a thorough affordability assessment before approving any EPM application. This assessment will consider:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>(a) Your current income and expenditure;</li>
          <li>(b) Your existing financial commitments and debts;</li>
          <li>(c) The impact of the EPM on your overall financial position;</li>
          <li>(d) Your ability to meet ongoing property obligations (insurance, council tax, maintenance);</li>
          <li>(e) Foreseeable changes to your circumstances (e.g., retirement, reduction in pension income);</li>
          <li>(f) The potential impact of interest rate changes on any variable-rate elements.</li>
        </ul>
        <p><strong>16.2</strong> We may request supporting documentation including bank statements, pension statements, tax returns, proof of benefits, and other evidence of income and expenditure.</p>
        <p><strong>16.3</strong> If our assessment indicates that the EPM may not be affordable or suitable for you, we will decline the application and, where appropriate, explain the reasons and suggest alternative options.</p>
        <p><strong>16.4</strong> We may also recommend that you seek independent financial advice from a qualified adviser regulated by the FCA.</p>
