        <h2>18. Financial Services Compensation Scheme (FSCS)</h2>
        <p><strong>18.1</strong> As an FCA-authorised firm, eligible claims against FutureProof Financial may be covered by the Financial Services Compensation Scheme (FSCS).</p>
        <p><strong>18.2</strong> The FSCS provides compensation if an authorised firm is unable to pay claims against it, for example because it has gone out of business.</p>
        <p><strong>18.3</strong> The current FSCS compensation limits are:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>(a) Deposits: up to £85,000 per eligible person, per firm;</li>
          <li>(b) Investments: up to £85,000 per eligible person, per firm;</li>
          <li>(c) Home finance (mortgage advice and arranging): unlimited.</li>
        </ul>
        <p><strong>18.4</strong> For further information about the FSCS, visit fscs.org.uk or call 0800 678 1100.</p>
